## 🔄 Automation Pipeline

### iOS Shortcut Workflow

```
TRIGGER: Album added to "Blog Albums"
  ↓
1. Get album metadata
   - Name
   - Photo count
   - Date created
   - Location (if available)
  ↓
2. Show notification
   [Write Story] [Later]
  ↓
3. If [Write Story]:
   - Select template
   - Guided prompts (template-specific)
   - Capture responses
  ↓
4. Process photos:
   - Download from iCloud
   - Resize (2000px width max)
   - Optimize (quality 85%)
   - Save to Obsidian/images/
  ↓
5. Generate markdown:
   - Frontmatter (title, date, tags, etc.)
   - Gallery syntax
   - Template structure
   - User's text inserted
  ↓
6. Save to Obsidian/drafts/
   [filename: YYYY-MM-DD-slug.md]
  ↓
7. iCloud sync (automatic)
```

### Telegram Bot Flow

```
USER: [Sends photo with caption]
  ↓
BOT (Sua):
  1. Download photo
  2. Extract caption
  3. Detect location (if shared)
  4. Suggest template based on keywords
     (café/coffee → Cafe Visit)
     (ramen/food → Food Experience)
  5. Prompt additional details if needed
  6. Create markdown draft
  7. Save to Obsidian/drafts/
  8. Confirm: "Draft created! Review in Obsidian"
```

### Git + Quartz Deploy

```
TRIGGER: File change in published/
  ↓
1. Obsidian Git plugin:
   - Auto-commit (every 5 min)
   - Push to GitHub
  ↓
2. GitHub Actions:
   - Detect push
   - Run: npx quartz build
   - Generate static site
   - Deploy to gh-pages branch
  ↓
3. GitHub Pages:
   - Serve from gh-pages
   - Live in ~2 min
```

